Khat destroyed as traders clash             Joseph Muchiri  13th Jun 2019 00:00:00 GMT +0300 Joseph Muchiri  13th Jun 2019 00:00:00 GMT +0300 Joseph Muchiri   Embu ward representatives from khat growing areas inspect some of the miraa that was reduced to waste after the stimulant traders from Embu and Meru Counties clashed at Kamuketha muguka market in Embu town on Tuesday night. Khat was worth over Sh1 million was destroyed while scores of traders sustained injuries. Police were deployed to contain the situation. [Joseph Muchiri/Standard]  Embu ward representatives from khat growing areas inspect some of the miraa that was reduced to waste after the stimulant traders from Embu and Meru Counties clashed at Kamuketha muguka market in Embu town on Tuesday night. Khat was worth over Sh1 million was destroyed while scores of traders sustained injuries. Police were deployed to contain the situation. [Joseph Muchiri/Standard] Embu ward representatives from khat growing areas inspect some of the miraa that was reduced to waste after the stimulant traders from Embu and Meru Counties clashed at Kamuketha muguka market in Embu town on Tuesday night. Khat was worth over Sh1 million was destroyed while scores of traders sustained injuries. Police were deployed to contain the situation. [Joseph Muchiri/Standard] Embu ward representatives from khat growing areas inspect some of the miraa that was reduced to waste after the stimulant traders from Embu and Meru Counties clashed at Kamuketha muguka market in Embu town on Tuesday night. Khat was worth over Sh1 million was destroyed while scores of traders sustained injuries. Police were deployed to contain the situation  googletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-1498022554617-0'); });    SEE ALSO :Embu farmers cry foul over Machakos high levies on muguka SEE ALSO : Embu farmers cry foul over Machakos high levies on muguka      SEE ALSO :Man alleged to have killed son over Sh500 denies murder charge SEE ALSO : Man 